 double game in Libya|first=Paul|last=Taylor|date=17 April 2019|website=POLITICO}}</ref><br>{{flag|United Arab Emirates}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.middleeastmonitor.com/20180302-un-team-uae-is-developing-its-air-base-in-eastern-libya/|title=UN team: UAE is developing its air base in eastern Libya|date=2 March 2018|website=Middle East Monitor}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-50302602|title=Foreign jet suspected in Libya migrant attack|first=Manisha|last=Ganguly|date=6 November 2019|via=www.bbc.com}}</ref><ref name=\"claims\" /><ref name=\"Elumami\"/><br>{{flag|Jordan}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.libyanexpress.com/jordan-arming-libyas-haftar-with-armored-vehicles-and-weapons/|title=Jordan arming Libya's Haftar with armored vehicles and weapons|date=23 May 2019}}</ref><br>{{flag|Syria}}<ref name=SAA>{{cite web|url=https://www.almasdarnews.com/article/benghazi-based-libyan-govt-sends-first-official-delegation-to-syria/|title=Benghazi-based Libyan gov\u2019t sends first official delegation to Syria|website=Al Masdar News|date=1 March 2020}}</ref>\n| combatant2        = {{flagicon|Libya}}{{flagicon image|The emblem on the passport of Libya.svg|border=no}} '''[[Government of National Accord]]'''\n* {{flagicon image|Flag of the Libyan Ground Forces.svg}} [[Libyan Army]]\n*{{flagicon image|Flag_of_the_Libyan_Navy.svg}} [[Libyan Navy]]<br>{{small|(GNA\u2013aligned)}}\n* {{flagicon image|Flag of the Libyan Air Force.svg}} [[Libyan Air Force]]<br>{{small|(GNA\u2013aligned)}}<ref name=\"express\" /><ref name=\"bbc1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-47840031|title=Fighting flares on outskirts of Tripoli|date=6 April 2019|work=[[BBC]]}}</ref>\n[[Tripoli Protection Force]]<ref name=\"mee\">{{cite web|url=https://www.middleeasteye.net/news/haftar-forces-capture-old-tripoli-airport-after-clashes-near-libyan-capital|title=Haftar forces capture old Tripoli airport after clashes near Libyan capital|work=Middle East Eye and a