ad of unity government)</small><br>{{flagicon|Libya}}{{flagicon image|The emblem on the passport of Libya.svg|border=no}} Maj. Gen. [[Osama al-Juwaili]]<br><small>(Joint operations room leader)</small><br>{{flagicon|Libya}}{{flagicon image|The emblem on the passport of Libya.svg|border=no}} Maj. Gen. Abdul Basset Marwan<ref>[https://www.voanews.com/a/violent-standoff-in-tripoli-civilians-displaced-suffering/4900433.html Violent Standoff in Tripoli; Civilians Displaced, Suffering]. Voice of America, 2 May 2019.</ref><br><small>(Tripoli Military Region commander)</small><br>{{flagicon|Libya}}{{flagicon image|The emblem on the passport of Libya.svg|border=no}} Emad al-Tarabelsi<ref name=\"express\" /><br><small>(Capital security commander)</small><br>{{flagicon|Libya}}{{flagicon image|The emblem on the passport of Libya.svg|border=no}} Atef Braqeek<br><small>(Tripoli Protection Force commander)</small><br>\n| units1            = See [[Order of battle for the 2019\u201320 Western Libya offensive#Pro-House of Representatives forces|order of battle]]\n| units2            = See [[Order of battle for the 2019\u201320 Western Libya offensive#Pro-Government of National Accord forces|order of battle]]\n| strength1         = {{flagicon|Libya}}{{flagicon image|Libyan COA used by Haftar.png|70px|border=no}} 3,000<ref name=\"bastion\">{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-libya-security-analysis-idUSKCN1TL241|title=In Libya's anti-Haftar bastion, a resolve to fight hardens|date=20 June 2019|via=www.reuters.com}}</ref><br />{{flagicon|Russia}}  200\u20131400 [[Wagner Group|Wagner PMC]]<ref name=\"auto\"/><ref name=\"auto3\"/><br>{{flagicon|Syria}} 300\u2013400<ref>[https://www.presstv.com/Detail/2020/04/19/623413/Everyone-is-looking-for-a-piece-of-Libya-during-its-civil-war]</ref><br />{{Flagicon|Sudan}} 3,000 Sudanese mercenaries<ref>{{cite web|author=Jason Burke |author2=Zeinab Mohammed Salih |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/dec/24/mercenaries-flock-to-libya-raising-fears-of-prolonged-war |title=Mercenaries flock to Libya raising fears of prolonged war |website=The Guardian |date= |accessdate=2020-01-15}}</ref>\n| strength2         = {{flagicon|Libya}}{{flagicon image|The emblem on the passport of Libya.svg|border=no}} 5,000 total<ref name=\"bastion\"/><ref name=\"SANA_WhoWhom_Tripoli\">{{cite web|last1=Lacher|first1=Wolfram|author1link= Wolfram Lacher|title=Who is fighting whom in Tripoli? How the 2019 civil war is transforming Libya's military landscape|website= Security Assessment in North Africa Briefing Paper|year=2019|url= http://www.smallarmssurvey.org/fileadmin/docs/T-Briefing-Papers/SAS-SANA-BP-Tripoli-2019.pdf|accessdate=11 November 2019|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20191110232900/http://www.smallarmssurvey.org/fileadmin/docs/T-Briefing-Papers/SAS-SANA-BP-Tripoli-2019.pdf|archivedate=10 November 2019|url-status=live <!-- live|dead|unfit|usurped -->}}</ref>\n*3,000 (in Tripoli) \n*2,000 (in Tripoli's surroundings)\n{{flagicon|Syrian opposition}} 5,300 (April 2020) <ref name=\"Guardian_2kSNA_helping_GNA\" /><ref name=\"Xinhuasyrianrebels\"/><ref>http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=160797</ref><br>{{Flagicon|Turkey}} 35 advisors<ref name=\"Guardian_2kSNA_helping_GNA\" />\n| casualties1       = {{flagicon|Libya}}{{flagicon image|Libyan COA used by Haftar.png|70px|border=no}} Unknown killed<br>{{flagicon|Libya}}{{flagicon image|Libyan COA used by Haftar.png|70px|border=no}} 1 MiG-21MF lost<ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/north-africa/2019/04/14/Haftar-forces-fighter-jet-downed-near-libya-capital-says-unity-government.html|title=Haftar forces' fighter jet downed near Libya capital, says unity government|website=english.alarabiya.net|accessdate=15 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.france24.com/en/20190415-libya-commander-haftar-egypts-sisi-fighting-tripoli|title=Libyan commander Haftar meets Egypt's Sisi as fighting erupts near Tripoli|date=15 April 2019|website=France 24|accessdate=15 April 2019}}</ref><br>{{flagicon|Russia}} 13\u201338 [[Private military company|PMC]]s killed<ref>[https://meduza.io/en/feature/2019/10/02/a-small-price-to-pay-for-tripoli A small price to pay for Tripoli Between 10 and 35 Russian mercenaries have been killed in the Libyan Civil War. We identified several of them.]</ref><ref>[https://madamasr.com/en/2019/12/28/feature/politics/from-tripolis-front-lines-how-haftar-recovered-from-the-setback-in-gharyan-and-whats-next-for-the-advancing-lna/ From Tripoli\u2019s front lines: How Haftar recovered from the setback in Gharyan and what\u2019s next for the advancing LNA]</ref><br>{{flagicon image|Flag of the United Arab Emirates.svg}} 6 soldiers killed <small>(per GNA; disputed)</small>{{Ref label|deaths|a}}\n| casualties2       = {{flagicon|Libya}}{{flagicon image|The emblem on the passport of Libya.svg|border=no}} 940 killed <small>(per LNA)</small><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.alhadath.net/alhadath/2019/12/27/\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u0645\u0627\u0631\u064a-\u0646\u0633\u062a\u0639\u062f-\u0644\u062f\u062e\u0648\u0644-\u0645\u0639\u0631\u0643\u0629-\u0627\u0644\u0623\u062d\u064a\u0627\u0621-\u0627\u0644\u0631\u0626\u064a\u0633\u064a\u0629-\u0628\u0637\u0631\u0627\u0628\u0644\u0633.html|title=\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u0645\u0627\u0631\u064a: \u0639\u0634\u0631\u0627\u062a \u0627\u0644\u062c\u062b\u062b \u0644\u0644\u0645\u064a\u0644\u064a\u0634\u064a\u0627\u062a \u0628\u0637\u0631\u064a\u0642 \u0645\u0637\u0627\u0631 \u0637\u0631\u0627\u0628\u0644\u0633|first=\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0631\u0628\u064a\u0629|last=\u0646\u062a|date=27 December 2019|website=\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0631\u0628\u064a\u0629 \u0646\u062a}}</ref><br />{{flagicon|Libya}}{{flagicon image|The emblem on the passport of Libya.svg|border=no}} 2 Mirage F1, 3 L-39, 1 helicopter & 12 Bayraktar UAVs lost<ref>2 Mirage F1,[http://en.alwasat.ly/news/libya/242982][https://www.reuters.com/article/us-libya-security-airplane/haftar-forces-shoot-down-tripoli-government-warplane-lna-video-shows-apparent-foreign-pilot-idUSKCN1SD1MB][https://sputniknews.com/africa/201905071074781244-libya-haftar-plane-down/] 3 L-39,[https://www.rt.com/news/456161-libya-plane-shot-down/][https://www.arabnews.com/node/1521111/middle-east][https://aviation-safety.net/wikibase/234692] 1 helicopter,[https://www.alaraby.co.uk/english/news/2019/6/13/haftars-forces-down-helicopter-killing-pilot-in-western-libya] 8 Bayraktar UAVs [https://madamasr.com/en/2019/12/28/feature/politics/from-tripolis-front-lines-how-haftar-recovered-from-the-setback-in-gharyan-and-whats-next-for-the-advancing-lna/][https://defpost.com/libyan-national-army-shoots-down-turkish-bayraktar-tb2-drone/]</ref><br />{{flagicon|Syrian opposition}} 199<ref>[http://www.syriahr.com/en/?p=160797 Turkey\u2019s involvement in Libya war: 7,400 Syrian mercenaries volunteer to go to Libya, nearly 200 of whom killed in Libyan territory so far]</ref>- 500 killed<ref>[https://aawsat.com/english/home/article/2212856/lna-says-turkish-battleship-strikes-area-western-libya LNA Says Turkish Battleship Strikes Area in Western Libya]</ref><br>{{Flagicon|Turkey}} 2<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-libya-security-turkey/erdogan-says-two-turkish-troops-killed-in-libya-conflict-idUSKCN20J0ST|title=Erdogan says two Turkish troops killed in Libya conflict|website=Reuters}}</ref>\u201323 killed<ref>[https://www.egypttoday.com/Article/2/81946/LNA-kills-16-Turkish-military-personnel-including-3-commanders LNA kills 16 Turkish military personnel including 3 commanders]<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-libya-security/eastern-libya-forces-say-16-turkish-soldiers-killed-in-fighting-idUSKCN20H0JX|title=Eastern Libya forces say 16 Turkish soldiers killed in fighting - Libya as Haftar\u2019s forces advance on Misrata|website=Reuters}}</ref><ref>[https://www.alarabiya.net/ar/north-africa/2020/02/28/\u0628\u0639\u062f-\u0627\u062f\u0644\u0628-7-\u0642\u062a\u0644\u0649-\u0623\u062a\u0631\u0627\u0643-\u0628\u0642\u0635\u0641-\u0627\u0644\u062c\u064a\u0634-\u0627\u0644\u0644\u064a\u0628\u064a-\u0639\u0644\u0649-\u0645\u0639\u064a\u062a\u064a\u0642\u0629 7 \u0642\u062a\u0644\u0649 \u0623\u062a\u0631\u0627\u0643 \u0628\u0642\u0635\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u062c\u064a\u0634 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064a\u0628\u064a \u0639\u0644\u0649 \u0645\u0639\u064a\u062a\u064a\u0642\u0629]</ref>\n| casualties3       = 2,356+ killed overall (2,000+ combatants and 356 civilians)<ref name=\"casualties\">{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/jan/14/libyan-warlord-haftar-leaves-moscow-without-signing-ceasefire-deal|title=Libyan warlord Haftar leaves Moscow without signing ceasefire deal|date=14 January 2020|agency=The Guardian}}<br>[https://unsmil.unmissions.org/one-year-destructive-war-libya-unsmil-renews-calls-immediate-cessation-hostilities-and-unity-combat ONE YEAR OF DESTRUCTIVE WAR IN LIBYA, UNSMIL RENEWS CALLS FOR IMMEDIATE CESSATION OF HOSTILITIES AND UNITY TO COMBAT COVID-19]</ref><br>146,000 displaced<ref name=\"casualties\"/><br />{{flagicon|Italy}} 1 [[Italy|Italian]] [[General Atomics MQ-9 Reaper|MQ-9 Reaper UAV]] lost<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofmalta.com/articles/view/pro-haftar-forces-in-libya-shoot-down-italian-drone.751345|title=Pro-Haftar forces in Libya 'shoot down Italian drone'|website=Times of Malta}}</ref><ref name=\"auto2\">{{cite web|url=https://theaviationist.com/2019/11/23/u-s-drone-lost-over-tripoli-the-day-after-italy-lost-a-predator-b-in-libya-new-jamming-capability-deployed/|title=U.S. Drone Lost Over Tripoli The Day After Italy Lost a Predator B in Libya: New Jamming Capability Deployed?|first=David|last=Cenciotti|date=23 November 2019}}</ref><br />{{flagicon|United States}} 1 [[United States|US]] [[General Atomics MQ-9 Reaper|MQ-9 Reaper UAV]] lost<ref name=\"auto2\"/><br />\n| notes             = {{Note label|deaths|a}} UAE announced the death of six soldiers in a car collision in Yemen. However, the GNA stated that they were killed by GNA airstrikes in Libya.<ref name=\"UAEC1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.libyanexpress.com/libyas-gna-air-force-destroys-haftars-defenses-at-al-jufra-airbase-6-uae-soldiers-killed/|title=Libya's GNA Air Force destroys Haftar's defenses at Al-Jufra airbase, 6 UAE soldiers killed|date=13 September 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"UAEC2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.middleeasteye.net/news/six-uae-soldier-killed-operations-field-accident-state-media|title=Six UAE soldiers killed in 'operations field' accident: State media|website=Middle East Eye}}</ref><ref name=\"UAEC3\">{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-yemen-security-idUSKCN1VY1QI|title=Six UAE servicemen killed in Yemen road accident|date=13 September 2019|via=www.reuters.com}}</ref>\n| campaignbox       = {{Campaignbox 2014 Libyan Civil War}}{{Campaignbox Libyan Crisis (2011\u2013present)}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Western Libya offensive''', code-named '''Operation Flood of Dignity''' ({{lang-ar|\u0639\u0645\u0644\u064a\u0629 \u0637\u0648\u0641\u0627\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0643\u0631\u0627\u0645\u0629}}), is a military campaign by the [[Libyan National Army]] under [[Field marshal (Libya)|Field Marshal]] [[Khalifa Haftar]], which represents the Libyan [[House of Representatives (Libya)|House of Representatives]], to capture the western region of [[Libya]] and eventually the capital [[Tripoli]] held by the [[UN Security Council]]-recognised [[Government of National Accord]].\n\nThe offensive has resulted in over 2,356 dead.<ref name=\"casualties\"/> It began on 4 April 2019,<ref name=\"econ\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.economist.com/middle-east-and-africa/2019/04/05/khalifa-haftar-libyas-strongest-warlord-makes-a-push-for-tripoli|title=Khalifa Haftar, Libya's strongest warlord, makes a push for Tripoli|date=5 April 2019|work=The Economist|access-date=5 April 2019|issn=0013-0613}}</ref> 10 days before the [[Libyan National Conference]] for organising [[2019 Libyan general election|presidential and parliamentary elections in Libya]] had been planned to take place,<ref name=\"NatConf_postponed\">{{cite news|last1=Zaptia|first1=Sami|title=UNSMIL postpones Ghadames National Conference until conditions are right |date=9 April 2019|work=[[Libya Herald]]|url=https://www.libyaherald.com/2019/04/09/unsmil-postpones-ghadames-national-conference-until-conditions-are-right/|accessdate=9 April 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190411033724/https://www.libyaherald.com/2019/04/09/unsmil-postpones-ghadames-national-conference-until-conditions-are-right/|archivedate=11 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> and five days after the first session of the [[2019 Libyan local elections]] was held successfully.<ref name=\"MEM_elections_March2019\"/>\n\n[[War crime]]s and [[crimes against humanity]] that take place during the conflict are covered by the mandate of the [[International Criminal Court investigation in Libya]] under [[United Nations Security Council Resolution 1970]].<ref name=\"HRW_ICC_jurisdiction\"/><ref name=\"Bensouda_20190417\"/>\n\n== Background ==\n{{See also|Libyan Civil War (2011)|Libyan Civil War (2014\u2013present)}}\nFollowing the overthrow and [[Death of Muammar Gaddafi|death]] of [[Muammar Gaddafi]] and the fall of the [[Great Socialist People's Libyan Arab Jamahiriya]] in 2011, political and military control in Libya were in a state of flux. Fighting between different factions escalated in 2014, with the [[House of Representatives (Libya)|House of Representatives]], based in the eastern city of Tobruk, being the main political force claiming to be the legitimate government of Libya. The House of Representatives was supported by Field Marshal [[Khalifa Haftar]]'s [[Libyan National Army]]. In early 2016 a rival government, the [[Government of National Accord]] (GNA), was established in Tripoli with the backing of the [[United Nations|UN]] and several countries.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.euronews.com/2019/04/05/libya-a-country-divided-from-gaddafi-to-haftar-how-did-they-get-here|title=Libya, a country divided: From Gaddafi to Haftar, how did they get here?|first=Jez|last=Fielder|date=5 April 2019|website=[[Euronews]]}}</ref> There were multiple attempts to negotiate between the two governments and organise [[2019 Libyan general election|new elections]] throughout 2017 and 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://madamasr.com/en/2017/02/25/feature/politics/haftar-and-sarraj-in-cairo-the-details-of-egypts-partially-successful-libyan-summit/|title=Haftar and Sarraj in Cairo: The details of Egypt's partially successful Libyan summit|date=25 February 2017|accessdate=5 April 2019|author1=Asmahan Soliman|author2=Hossam Bahgat|work=[[Mada Masr]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thenational.ae/opinion/libyan-peace-may-be-possible-after-abu-dhabi-talks-1.27135|title=Libyan peace may be possible after Abu Dhabi talks|website=[[The National (Abu Dhabi)|The National]]|date=8 May 2017|accessdate=5 April 2019|author=Mustafa Fetouri}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.libyanexpress.com/libya-elections-by-june-2019-un-envoy-tells-reuters-at-palermo-conference/|title=Libya elections by June 2019, UN envoy tells Reuters at Palermo Conference|website=Libyan Express|language=en-GB|access-date=1 February 2019|date=12 November 2018}}</ref> Haftar and GNA Prime Minister [[Fayez al-Sarraj]] met and spoke with each other twice for negotiations, in November 2018 and February 2019.<ref name=\"aj1\" /> The [[Supreme Judicial Council of Libya]], created in 2011,<ref name=\"ICJ_SJC_challenges\">{{cite web | title =Challenges for the Libyan Judiciary: Ensuring Independence, Accountability and Gender Equality | trans-title= | website= [[International Commission of Jurists]] |year = 2016 | url = https://www.icj.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Libya-Challenges-the-Judiciary-Publications-Reports-Thematic-report-2016-ENG.pdf |format =PDF | accessdate = 14 October 2019 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20191014003141/https://www.icj.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Libya-Challenges-the-Judiciary-Publications-Reports-Thematic-report-2016-ENG.pdf |archivedate= 14 October 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> retained its structure as a single national body despite the political split,<ref name=\"LHerald_SJC_elections_Tripoli\">{{cite news | last1= Zaptia | first1= Sami | title= After new elections, members of Libya\u2019s Supreme Judiciary Council hold first meeting in Tripoli |trans-title = | date= 7 October 2019 | newspaper= [[Libya Herald]] | url= https://www.libyaherald.com/2019/10/07/after-new-elections-members-of-libyas-supreme-judiciary-council-hold-first-meeting-in-tripoli/ |accessdate=13 October 2019 |archiveurl= http://archive.wikiwix.com/cache/index2.php?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.libyaherald.com%2F2019%2F10%2F07%2Fafter-new-elections-members-of-libyas-supreme-judiciary-council-hold-first-meeting-in-tripoli%2F |archivedate= 13 October 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> and in 2019 went through Libya-wide \"transparent elections\" and a \"peaceful transfer of power\".<ref name=\"UNSMIL_SJC_congrats2019\">{{cite web | title =UNSMIL congratulates the newly elected members of the Supreme Judicial Council in Libya | trans-title= | website= [[United Nations Support Mission in Libya|UNSMIL]] |date =10 July 2019 | url = https://unsmil.unmissions.org/unsmil-congratulates-newly-elected-members-supreme-judicial-council-libya | accessdate = 14 October 2019 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20191014020130/https://unsmil.unmissions.org/unsmil-congratulates-newly-elected-members-supreme-judicial-council-libya |archivedate= 14 October 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nFace-to-face consultations with 7,000 Libyans and online consultations with 130,000 Libyans during 2018\u20132019, coordinated by the [[United Nations Support Mission in Libya]] (UNSMIL) and the [[Centre for Humanitarian Dialogue]], led to a plan to hold the [[Libyan National Conference]] in [[Ghadames]] during 14\u201316 April 2019 in order to recommend to the Libyan [[House of Representatives (Libya)|House of Representatives]] and [[High Council of State (Libya)|High Council of State]] methods and dates for holding [[2019 Libyan general election|2019 presidential and parliamentary elections]] in Libya.<ref name=\"NatConf_postponed\" /> The first batch of the [[2019 Libyan local elections|2019 municipal elections in Libya]] took place on 30 March 2019.<ref name=\"MEM_elections_March2019\">{{cite news| title=Libya holds municipal elections in first vote for five years| date=31 March 2019| publisher=[[Middle East Monitor]]| url=https://www.middleeastmonitor.com/20190331-libya-holds-municipal-elections-in-first-vote-for-five-years/| accessdate=20 April 2019| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401122341/https://www.middleeastmonitor.com/20190331-libya-holds-municipal-elections-in-first-vote-for-five-years/| archivedate=1 April 2019| url-status=live| df=dmy-all}}</ref> Other aims of the conference, to which representatives of all political factions were invited, included creating a unity government between Sarraj and Haftar and proposing a framework for creating a new constitution.<ref name=\"Bloomberg\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2019-04-06/libyan-air-force-strikes-haftar-positions-south-of-tripoli|title=Libya Lurches Toward Battle for Capital as Sarraj Vows to Fight|date=6 April 2019|work=[[Bloomberg News]]}}</ref> In March 2019, the [[2019 Southern Libya offensive|advance of Haftar's forces in southern Libya]] during the preceding few months started to cause concern for the organisers of the conference.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/mar/21/un-libya-envoy-hopes-reconciliation-talks-will-bring-stability|title=UN Libya envoy hopes reconciliation talks will bring stability|author=Patrick Wintour|date=21 March 2019|work=[[The Guardian]]}}</ref> [[Ghassan Salam\u00e9]], head of UNSMIL, stated on 4 April 2019 that the conference would be postponed because of the outburst of military events, but that it would be held <blockquote>\"as soon as possible because we do not have the right to allow this historic opportunity to be corrupted. At the same time, we cannot ask for the presence of the Conference, with the [cannons] firing and the raids ongoing, without making sure that all those who are willing to respond to this historic national duty from all regions of the country are able to ensure their safety and freedom by expressing their opinion.\"<ref name=\"NatConf_postponed\" /></blockquote>\n\nOn 4 April 2019, an audio recording was published on Facebook by Marshal Haftar declaring war on the UN-recognised Government of National Accord and announcing that the LNA would militarily take over the capital city Tripoli.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.libyaobserver.ly/news/khalifa-haftar-declares-war-tripoli|title=Khalifa Haftar declares war on Tripoli|work=[[The Libya Observer]]|date=4 April 2019|accessdate=5 April 2019|author=Abdulkader Assad}}</ref> In response, the government in Tripoli, led by Prime Minister Fayez al-Sarraj and the [[Presidential Council (Libya)|Presidential Council]] ordered a general mobilisation of all of its [[Libyan Army|security forces]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.middleeastmonitor.com/20190404-libya-declares-mobilization-to-face-haftars-forces/|title=Libya declares mobilisation to face Haftar's forces|date=4 April 2019|website=Middle East Monitor}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.euronews.com/2019/04/04/tensions-flare-in-libya-as-eastern-libyan-commander-orders-forces-to-move-on-tripoli|title=Tensions flare in Libya as eastern Libyan commander orders forces to move on Tripoli|author1=Alexander Morgan|author2=Matthew Holroyd|date=5 April 2019|website=[[Euronews]]}}</ref> On 6 April, Prime Minister Sarraj, as supreme commander of the Libyan Army, created a joint operations room under the western military region commander, Major General [[Osama al-Juwaili]], to coordinate their operations.<ref>[https://www.libyaobserver.ly/inbrief/pc-president-forms-joint-military-operations-room-war-rocks-tripoli-yet-again PC President forms joint military operations room as war rocks Tripoli yet again]. ''Libya Observer''. Published 6 April 2019. Retrieved 30 April 2019.</ref>\n\n=== International (non-UNSMIL) ===\nFrom early 2015, during the years prior to the April 2019 attack on Tripoli, Haftar received long-term support from French authorities, including French \"advisers, clandestine operatives, and special forces\"<ref name=\"ForeignAff_FR_warlord\">{{cite web | last1 =Harchaoui | first1 =Jalel | title =How France Is Making Libya Worse | publisher = [[Foreign Affairs]] | date = 21 September 2017 | url = https://www.foreignaffairs.com/articles/france/2017-09-21/how-france-making-libya-worse | url-access = limited | accessdate = 19 April 2019 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20190419204437/https://www.foreignaffairs.com/articles/france/2017-09-21/how-france-making-libya-worse |archivedate= 19 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> helping the LNA's military operations in the east and south of Libya.<ref name=\"Bloomberg_FR_IT_roles\" /><ref name=\"FOfEur_FR_specforces\">{{cite web | last1 = Fitzgerald | first1 = Mary | title = Is Libya on the brink of yet another civil war?  | publisher = [[Friends of Europe]] | date = 12 April 2019 | url = https://friendsofeurope.org/publication/libya-brink-yet-another-civil-war | accessdate = 19 April 2019 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20190419204456/https://friendsofeurope.org/publication/libya-brink-yet-another-civil-war |archivedate= 19 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> Three of the French special-forces soldiers died in a helicopter accident near Benghazi in July 2016.<ref name=\"ForeignAff_FR_warlord\" /> ''[[Bloomberg News]]'' stated that the al-Sarraj administration had long-term support from Italian authorities.<ref name=\"Bloomberg_FR_IT_roles\">{{cite news|title=France and Italy Should Lead on Libya \u2013 Apart from Libyans themselves, they have most to lose if things get any worse|date=11 April 2019|work=[[Bloomberg News]]|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/articles/2019-04-11/libya-conflict-france-and-italy-should-stop-squabbling-and-lead|accessdate=15 April 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190414231930/https://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/articles/2019-04-11/libya-conflict-france-and-italy-should-stop-squabbling-and-lead|archivedate=14 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> ''[[The Economist]]'' argued that a May 2018 meeting between al-Sarraj and Haftar, hosted by French president [[Emmanuel Macron]] in the context of French-Italian rivalry with regards to Libya, \"undermined\" the efforts of Ghassan Salam\u00e9 in facilitating the organising of the [[Libyan National Conference]] by Libyans. ''The Economist'' pointed to the [[Greenstream pipeline]] natural gas pipeline and French and Italian [[petroleum|crude oil]] interests in Libya as significant factors in the two countries' relations with Libyan political forces in 2018.<ref name=\"Economist_2manycooks\">{{cite news|title=Too many cooks \u2013 Libya's feuds cross the Mediterranean|date=8 November 2018|work=[[The Economist]]|url=https://www.economist.com/middle-east-and-africa/2018/11/08/libyas-feuds-cross-the-mediterranean|accessdate=15 April 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181210191502/https://www.economist.com/middle-east-and-africa/2018/11/08/libyas-feuds-cross-the-mediterranean|archivedate=10 December 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n''[[Bloomberg News]]'' described [[Russia]], [[Egypt]] and the [[United Arab Emirates]] as \"backers\" of Haftar.<ref name=\"Bloomberg_FR_IT_roles\" /> Prior to the LNA attack on Tripoli, the [[Saudi Arabia]]n government gave twenty million US dollars to the LNA in support of the attack, \"to buy the loyalty of tribal leaders, recruit and pay fighters, and other military purposes.\"<ref name=\"AJE_WSJ_KSA_funds_attack\">{{cite news|title=Saudis 'gave Libya's Haftar millions of dollars before offensive'|date=13 April 2019|publisher=[[Al Jazeera English]]|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/04/saudis-gave-libya-haftar-millions-dollars-offensive-190412175708363.html|accessdate=14 April 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190413061249/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/04/saudis-gave-libya-haftar-millions-dollars-offensive-190412175708363.html|archivedate=13 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 27 December 2019  ''Bloomberg News'' reported that Turkey intended to deploy its navy to protect Tripoli and send troops to help train GNA forces. Additionally Turkmen rebel groups fighting in northern Syria were expected to transfer to Tripoli.<ref name=bl-20201227>{{cite news |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2019-12-27/turkey-backed-syrian-rebels-to-join-libya-war-against-haftar |title=Turkish Navy to Guard Tripoli as Syrian Rebels May Join War |author1=Selcan Hacaoglu |author2=Samer Al-Atrush |publisher=Bloomberg News |date=27 December 2019 |access-date=2 January 2020}}</ref><ref name=guardian-20200102>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/jan/02/turkish-parliament-to-vote-on-sending-troops-to-libya |title=Turkish parliament to vote on sending troops to Libya |agency=Associated Press |newspaper=The Guardian |date=2 January 2020 |access-date=2 January 2020}}</ref> By 29 December, 650 [[Turkish-backed Free Syrian Army]] personnel (also called: ''Syrian National Army'') had arrived in Libya and were stationed on the eastern frontline in Tripoli.<ref name=\"Guardian_2kSNA_helping_GNA\">{{cite news | last1= McKernan | first1= Bethan | last2= Akoush | first2=Hussein | title= Exclusive: 2,000 Syrian fighters deployed to Libya to support government | date= 2020-01-15 |newspaper= [[The Guardian]] | url= https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/jan/15/exclusive-2000-syrian-troops-deployed-to-libya-to-support-regime |accessdate=2020-01-17 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20200115054635/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/jan/15/exclusive-2000-syrian-troops-deployed-to-libya-to-support-regime |archivedate= 2020-01-15 |url-status=live <!-- live|dead|unfit|usurped --> |url-access = <!-- (subscription/registration/limited) default=free -->}}</ref>\n\n== The campaign ==\n{{see also|Timeline of the Libyan Civil War (2014\u2013present)|Libyan peace process#Salam\u00e9 three-point peace plan}}\n\n===2019===\n====April====\n;4 April\nOn the first day of the offensive, 4 April 2019, the LNA captured [[Gharyan]].<ref name=\"theguardian\">{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/apr/04/un-chief-urges-restraint-as-libyan-army-leader-plans-tripoli-assault|title=Libyan strongman orders troops to march on Tripoli|website=The Guardian|accessdate=5 April 2019}}</ref> Haftar urged pro-GNA militias to surrender, saying \"Those who lay down their weapons are safe, and those who raise the white banner are safe.\"<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/04/chief-deeply-concerned-military-escalation-libya-190404081217912.html|title=Libya: High alert in Tripoli after renegade leader orders advance|work=[[Al Jazeera]]|access-date=5 April 2019}}</ref> Interior minister Fathi Bashagha condemned the offensive, declaring that \"We will not be subdued by any use of force by any side or any person. And if anyone is willing to use force against us we're ready for sacrifice but we will not give up on democracy which we've always wanted from the beginning.\"<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n;5 April\nOn 5 April, the Libyan National Army stated that they had captured Qasr ben Ghashir, Wadi al-Rabie and Suq al-Khamis.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-libya-security-advance-idUSKCN1RH24V|title=Eastern Libyan forces say they control areas near Tripoli|date=5 April 2019|work=Reuters|access-date=5 April 2019|language=en}}</ref> LNA then marched toward [[Tripoli]] from several directions, reaching the city's outskirts after receiving orders to capture the city.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.afp.com/en/news/15/pro-haftar-militia-forces-reach-outskirts-tripoli-doc-1fd5e05|title=Pro-Haftar militia forces reach outskirts of Tripoli|work=[[Agence France-Presse]]|language=en|access-date=5 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-47819952|title=Libya general tells forces to take capital|date=5 April 2019|access-date=5 April 2019|language=en-GB|work=[[BBC]]}}</ref> The LNA reported asserting control over the town of [[Azizia]].<ref name=\"econ\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.alwasat.ly/news/libya/240912|title=LNA Spox: Army forces reached Aziziya.. have begun to implement the second part of the plan|website=Alwasat News|language=en|access-date=5 April 2019}}</ref> The LNA briefly captured a key checkpoint, known as Gate 27, on the road between Tripoli and [[Tunisia]], but withdrew overnight.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-libya-security-idUKKCN1RH0SK|title=U.N. chief to meet eastern Libya commander as fighters close in on...|date=5 April 2019|work=Reuters|access-date=5 April 2019|language=en}}</ref> The GNA interior ministry ordered all of its forces to be placed on maximum alert.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sunnewsonline.com/libya-troops-on-maximum-alert-as-rival-army-closes-in/|title=Libya troops on maximum alert as rival army closes in|date=5 April 2019|website=The Sun Nigeria|language=en-US|access-date=5 April 2019}}</ref> The [[United Nations Security Council]] scheduled an emergency meeting on the same day to discuss the recent developments in Libya.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://armenpress.am/eng/news/970164.html|title=UN Security Council to hold emergency meeting on Libya|website=armenpress.am|language=en|access-date=5 April 2019}}</ref> Later in the day the LNA reported capturing the village of Suq al-Khamis, located {{Convert|20|km|m}} south of Tripoli, after clashes with pro-GNA militias.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/libya-security-village/refile-eastern-forces-take-control-of-village-south-of-tripoli-after-clashes-resident-idUSL8N21N57Z|title=Eastern forces take control of village south of Tripoli after clashes - resident|agency=Reuters|date=April 5, 2019}}</ref> Meanwhile, the leader of the LNA, Field Marshal [[Khalifa Haftar]], met with UN Secretary General [[Ant\u00f3nio Guterres]] in the former's office in [[Tobruk]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.arabnews.com/node/1478066/middle-east|title=UN chief issues stark Libya warning as fighting rages south of Tripoli|date=6 April 2019|website=Arab News|language=en|access-date=6 April 2019}}</ref> During the late hours of the day a battle broke out over [[Tripoli International Airport]], in which LNA forces were able to successfully capture the airfield and defend it from a GNA counter-attack.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/AlArabiya_Brk/status/1114272901014917123|title=\u0631\u0648\u064a\u062a\u0631\u0632 \u0646\u0642\u0644\u0627 \u0639\u0646 \u0634\u0647\u0648\u062f \u0639\u064a\u0627\u0646: \u0627\u0644\u062c\u064a\u0634 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064a\u0628\u064a \u0645\u0627 \u0632\u0627\u0644 \u064a\u0633\u064a\u0637\u0631 \u0639\u0644\u0649 \u0645\u0637\u0627\u0631 \u0637\u0631\u0627\u0628\u0644\u0633 \u0627\u0644\u062f\u0648\u0644\u064a #\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0631\u0628\u064a\u0629_\u0639\u0627\u062c\u0644|last=\u0639\u0627\u062c\u0644|first=\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0631\u0628\u064a\u0629|date=5 April 2019|website=@AlArabiya_Brk|language=ar|access-date=6 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n;6 April\nOn 6 April, the LNA air force declared western Libya a no-fly zone<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tass.com/world/1052444|title=Libyan National Army declares no-fly zone in the west of the country|website=TASS|language=en|access-date=6 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.addresslibya.com/archives/59948|title=\u0639\u0627\u062c\u0644{{!}} \u0639\u0645\u0644\u064a\u0627\u062a \u0627\u0644\u0642\u0648\u0627\u062a \u0627\u0644\u062c\u0648\u064a\u0629 \u062a\u0639\u0644\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0646\u0637\u0642\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u063a\u0631\u0628\u064a\u0629 \u0645\u0646\u0637\u0642\u0629 \u0639\u0645\u0644\u064a\u0627\u062a \u0639\u0633\u0643\u0631\u064a\u0629 \u064a\u0645\u0646\u0639 \u0627\u0644\u0637\u064a\u0631\u0627\u0646 \u0641\u064a\u0647\u0627|date=6 April 2019|website=\u0635\u062d\u064a\u0641\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0646\u0648\u0627\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064a\u0628\u064a\u0629|language=ar|access-date=6 April 2019}}</ref> and began to engage GNA targets,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/AlainBRK/status/1114459394266357760|title=\u0639\u0627\u062c\u0644 {{!}} \u0645\u0635\u062f\u0631 \u0639\u0633\u0643\u0631\u064a: \u0633\u0644\u0627\u062d \u0627\u0644\u062c\u0648 \u0641\u064a #\u0627\u0644\u062c\u064a\u0634_\u0627\u0644\u0644\u064a\u0628\u064a \u064a\u0628\u062f\u0623 \u0641\u064a \u062a\u0646\u0641\u064a\u0630 \u0645\u0647\u0627\u0645\u0647 \u0636\u0645\u0646 \u0639\u0645\u0644\u064a\u0629 #\u062a\u062d\u0631\u064a\u0631_\u0637\u0631\u0627\u0628\u0644\u0633. #\u0644\u064a\u0628\u064a\u0627|last=\u0639\u0627\u062c\u0644|first=\u0627\u0644\u0639\u064a\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062e\u0628\u0627\u0631\u064a\u0629-|date=6 April 2019|website=@AlainBRK|language=ar|access-date=6 April 2019}}</ref> after GNA jets targeted LNA positions in Mizdah and Suq al-Khamis.<ref name=\"express\">{{cite web|url=https://www.libyanexpress.com/libyas-western-air-force-strikes-haftars-forces-positioned-in-mizda-sooq-al-khamis/|title=Libya's western Air Force strikes Haftar's forces positioned in Mizda, Sooq al-Khamis|website=Libyan Express|language=en-GB|access-date=6 April 2019|date=6 April 2019}}</ref> Haftar issued orders against using the LNA's aircraft in battle.<ref name=\"Bloomberg\" /> The LNA reported recapturing Gate 27,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/AlainBRK/status/1114260652254797825|title=\u0639\u0627\u062c\u0644 {{!}} \u0642\u0648\u0627\u062a \u0627\u0644\u062c\u064a\u0634 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064a\u0628\u064a \u062a\u062a\u0645\u0643\u0646 \u0645\u0646 \u0627\u0633\u062a\u0639\u0627\u062f\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0633\u064a\u0637\u0631\u0629 \u0639\u0644\u0649 \u0628\u0648\u0627\u0628\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0640 27 \u0641\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0627\u0635\u0645\u0629 #\u0637\u0631\u0627\u0628\u0644\u0633|last=\u0639\u0627\u062c\u0644|first=\u0627\u0644\u0639\u064a\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062e\u0628\u0627\u0631\u064a\u0629-|date=5 April 2019|website=@AlainBRK|language=ar|access-date=6 April 2019}}</ref> as well as asserting control over Salah al-Din<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/AlainBRK/status/1114449456232050688|title=\u0639\u0627\u062c\u0644 {{!}} \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0648\u0627\u0621 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0627\u0633\u0639 #\u062a\u0631\u0647\u0648\u0646\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0627\u0628\u0639 \u0644\u0640 #\u0627\u0644\u062c\u064a\u0634_\u0627\u0644\u0644\u064a\u0628\u064a \u064a\u0639\u0644\u0646 \u062a\u0642\u062f\u0645\u0647 \u0628\u0627\u062a\u062c\u0627\u0647 \u062d\u064a \u0635\u0644\u0627\u062d \u0627\u0644\u062f\u064a\u0646 \u062c\u0646\u0648\u0628 #\u0637\u0631\u0627\u0628\u0644\u0633. #\u0644\u064a\u0628\u064a\u0627|last=\u0639\u0627\u062c\u0644|first=\u0627\u0644\u0639\u064a\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062e\u0628\u0627\u0631\u064a\u0629-|date=6 April 2019|website=@AlainBRK|language=ar|access-date=6 April 2019}}</ref> and Ain Zara neighbourhood in southern Tripoli,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/SkyNewsArabia_B/status/1114460186532614155|title=\u0645\u0635\u0627\u062f\u0631\u0646\u0627: \u0627\u0644\u062c\u064a\u0634 \u0627\u0644\u0648\u0637\u0646\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064a\u0628\u064a \u064a\u062f\u062e\u0644 \u0623\u062d\u064a\u0627\u0621 {\u0639\u064a\u0646 \u0632\u0627\u0631\u0629} \u062c\u0646\u0648\u0628\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0627\u0635\u0645\u0629 \u0637\u0631\u0627\u0628\u0644\u0633|last=\u0639\u0631\u0628\u064a\u0629-\u0627\u0644\u0622\u0646|first=\u0633\u0643\u0627\u064a \u0646\u064a\u0648\u0632|date=6 April 2019|website=@SkyNewsArabia_B|language=ar|access-date=6 April 2019}}</ref> after pro-GNA militias surrendered to the LNA.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/AlArabiya_Brk/status/1114500448118104066|title=\u0645\u0635\u0627\u062f\u0631 \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0631\u0628\u064a\u0629: \u0627\u0633\u062a\u0633\u0644\u0627\u0645 \u0639\u0646\u0627\u0635\u0631 \u0644\u0642\u0648\u0627\u062a \u0627\u0644\u0648\u0641\u0627\u0642 \u0641\u064a \u0645\u0646\u0637\u0642\u0629 \u0639\u064a\u0646 \u062f\u0627\u0631\u0629 \u0641\u064a \u0637\u0631\u0627\u0628\u0644\u0633 #\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0631\u0628\u064a\u0629_\u0639\u0627\u062c\u0644|last=\u0639\u0627\u062c\u0644|first=\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0631\u0628\u064a\u0629|date=6 April 2019|website=@AlArabiya_Brk|language=ar|access-date=6 April 2019}}</ref> By nightfall forces loyal to the GNA launched a counterattack on the airport in southern Tripoli,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/middle_east/libyan-warplanes-target-forces-of-renegade-commander-on-tripoli-outskirts/2019/04/06/067cd318-5867-11e9-aa83-504f086bf5d6_story.html|title=Libyan warlord battles for control of Tripoli airport as militia forces push closer to city|work=[[Washington Post]]|author=Fahmi Hussein|date=6 April 2019|accessdate=6 April 2019}}</ref> which was repelled by the advancing LNA, according to Haftar.<ref>{{Cite tweet|user=LiBya_73|number=1114671539356688384|title=\u0645\u0637\u0627\u0631 \u0637\u0631\u0627\u0628\u0644\u0633 \u062a\u0645 \u062a\u0623\u0645\u064a\u0646\u0647 \u0628\u0627\u0644\u0643\u0627\u0645\u0644 \u0647\u0648 \u0648 \u0645\u062d\u064a\u0637\u0647 \u0645\u0646 \u0642\u0628\u0644 \u0643\u062a\u0627\u0626\u0628 \u0627\u0644\u062c\u064a\u0634 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064a\u0628\u064a \u0648\u0627\u0644\u062c\u064a\u0634 \u0645\u062a\u0642\u062f\u0645 \u0627\u0644\u0649 \u0645\u0627\u0628\u0639\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0637\u0627\u0631 \u0641\u0643\u0648\u0643\u0645 \u0645\u0646 \u0635\u0641\u062d\u0627\u062a \u0627\u0644\u0627\u062e\u0648\u0627\u0646 \u0648 \u0642\u0646\u0648\u0627\u062a\u0647\u0645 .. \u0644\u0648 \u062a\u0628\u0648 \u062a\u0633\u062a\u0645\u0639\u0648\u0627 \u0644\u0647\u0645 \u0645\u0639\u0646\u0627\u0647\u0627 \u0645\u0644\u064a\u0634\u064a\u0627\u062a\u0647\u0645 \u0639\u0644\u0649 \u0627\u0628\u0648\u0627\u0628 \u0627\u0644\u0642\u064a\u0627\u062f\u0629 \u0641\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0631\u062c\u0645\u0629|work=[[Twitter]]|date=6 April 2019|accessdate=6 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n;7 April\nA US military contingent and a contingent of Indian police peacekeepers were evacuated from Tripoli.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-47844513|title=Fighting near Libyan capital leaves 21 dead|date=8 April 2019|via=www.bbc.com}}</ref>\n\nColonel Mohamed Gnounou, the GNA military spokesman, announced that they started a counteroffensive to reclaim the territories in Tripoli taken by the LNA, dubbed ''\"Operation Volcano of Anger\"''. The UN mission in Libya asked for a two-hour ceasefire in south Tripoli to evacuate civilians.<ref>[https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/04/libya-gna-forces-announce-counteroffensive-defend-tripoli-190407121535177.html Libya's GNA forces announce 'counteroffensive' to defend Tripoli]. Al Jazeera. Published 7 April 2019.</ref><ref name=\"observ\" />\n\nIn an official declaration, the Ministry of Health of the GNA declared their casualties at 21 dead and 27 wounded.<ref>{{Cite tweet|user=AlkhaleejOnline|number=1114885205863673856|title=#Libya Local sources: the Ministry of Health of the Government of the Accord declares the death toll to 21 and the wounded to 27.|date=7 April 2019|work=Twitter}}</ref>\n\nThe LNA conducted an airstrike against a GNA position in southern Tripoli, the [[Bab al-Azizia]] military compound,<ref>Yeranian, Edward (7 April 2019). [https://www.voanews.com/a/un-calls-for-urgent-libya-truce-to-evacuate-civilians-wounded/4865342.html UN Appeals for Humanitarian Truce in Libya]. ''[[Voice of America]]''.</ref> the first LNA airstrike to target a part of the city.<ref name=\":3\">{{cite web|url=https://www.france24.com/en/20190407-libya-haftar-forces-air-strike-tripoli-gaddafi-usa|title=Haftar's forces claim air strike on Tripoli suburb as Libya crisis escalates|date=7 April 2019|website=France 24|language=en|access-date=7 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.alaraby.co.uk/english/news/2019/4/7/haftar-forces-launch-first-airstrike-on-libyas-capital|title=Haftar forces launch airstrike on Tripoli as Libyan, as government announces counter-offensive|website=The New Arab|language=en|access-date=7 April 2019}}</ref><ref name=\":2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.lbcgroup.tv/news/regional/437329/haftar-forces-conduct-air-strike-on-tripoli-as-un/en|title=Haftar forces conduct air strike on Tripoli as UN calls for truce|website=LBCI Lebanon|language=en|access-date=7 April 2019}}</ref> It is thought that Haftar has a superior air force, supplied by the United Arab Emirates,<ref>Patrick Wintour and Chris Steven (7 April 2019). [https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/apr/07/libya-us-forces-evacuated-haftar-seeks-military-control US forces evacuated from Libya as Haftar seeks military control]. ''The Guardian''.</ref> although the [[Libyan Air Force]] is nominally loyal to the GNA.<ref name=\"bbc1\" />\n\nBy the end of the day, an LNA spokesman, Major General al-Mesmari, reported that the LNA reached the Fernaj neighbourhood of Tripoli and are advancing through the eastern neighbourhoods of the city.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/AlainBRK/status/1114928427545448449|title=\u0639\u0627\u062c\u0644 {{!}} \u0627\u0644\u0645\u062a\u062d\u062f\u062b \u0628\u0627\u0633\u0645 \u0627\u0644\u062c\u064a\u0634 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064a\u0628\u064a: \u0642\u0648\u0627\u062a\u0646\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u0644\u062d\u0629 \u0639\u0644\u0649 \u0645\u0634\u0627\u0631\u0641 \u0645\u0646\u0637\u0642\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0641\u0631\u0646\u0627\u062c \u0641\u064a #\u0637\u0631\u0627\u0628\u0644\u0633. #\u0644\u064a\u0628\u064a\u0627|last=\u0639\u0627\u062c\u0644|first=\u0627\u0644\u0639\u064a\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062e\u0628\u0627\u0631\u064a\u0629-|date=7 April 2019|website=@AlainBRK|language=ar|access-date=7 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/AlArabiya_Brk/status/1114968103299973123|title=\u0627\u0644\u0644\u0648\u0627\u0621 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u0645\u0627\u0631\u064a \u0644\u0644\u0639\u0631\u0628\u064a\u0629: \u0642\u0648\u0627\u062a\u0646\u0627 \u062a\u062a\u0642\u062f\u0645 \u0646\u062d\u0648 \u0627\u0644\u0623\u062d\u064a\u0627\u0621 \u0627\u0644\u0631\u0626\u064a\u0633\u064a\u0629 \u0634\u0631\u0642 \u0637\u0631\u0627\u0628\u0644\u0633 #\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0631\u0628\u064a\u0629_\u0639\u0627\u062c|last=\u0639\u0627\u062c\u0644|first=\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0631\u0628\u064a\u0629|date=7 April 2019|website=@AlArabiya_Brk|language=ar|access-date=7 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n;8 April-9 April\nThe [[Government of National Accord|GNA]] airforce launched an air strike on the early hours of Monday on al-Watiyah, the only airbase captured by [[Libyan National Army|LNA]] since the launch of the operation, located 130 kilometres (80 miles) southeast of Tripoli.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/africa/un-backed-libya-govt-jets-strike-haftar-s-airbase/1444950|title=UN-backed Libya gov't jets strike Haftar's airbase|website=aa.com.tr}}</ref>\n\nAs part of the operation ''Volcano of Anger'' launched by [[Government of National Accord|GNA]], Mistrata militias mobilized on the frontlines of [[Tripoli]] to prevent the [[Libyan National Army|LNA]] from capturing it.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://aawsat.com/english/home/article/1669711/misrata-militias-mobilize-save-libya%E2%80%99s-sarraj|title=Misrata Militias Mobilize to Save Libya's Sarraj|website=Asharq AL-awsat}}</ref>\n\nLNA forces under Hifter conducted an airstrike against the GNA-held [[Mitiga International Airport]] in Tripoli, Libya's last functioning civilian airport, on 8 April.<ref name=\"reutersapril9look\"/><ref name=IvesKirkpatrick>{{cite web|author=Mike Ives & David D. Kirkpatrick|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/09/world/middleeast/libya-airport-airstrike-mitiga.html|newspaper=New York Times|title=Tripoli's Last Civilian Airport Reopens After Militias Mobilize Against Hifter|date=April 9, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/04/tripoli-functional-airport-hit-air-raid-clashes-rage-190408133455465.html|title=Tripoli's only functional airport hit by air raid as clashes rage|website=Al Jazeera|date=9 April 2019}}</ref> The closure left Misrata Airport, located 200&nbsp;km (125 miles) to the east down the coast, as the nearest airport for Tripoli residents.<ref name=\"reutersapril9look\" /> UN special representative for Libya [[Ghassan Salam\u00e9]] condemned the attack as \"a serious violation of [[international humanitarian law]].\"<ref name=IvesKirkpatrick/> Wolfram Lacher, a scholar of Libya at the [[German Institute for International and Security Affairs]], said that the strike showed Hifter's willingness \"to reduce Tripoli to rubble so that he can rule Libya, which is the only option he has left now anyway.\"<ref name=IvesKirkpatrick/> Flights were temporarily suspended; by 9 April, a coalition of local and regional militias<ref name=IvesKirkpatrick/> and GNA forces<ref name=\"reutersapril9look\"/> had pushed Hifter's forces from the airport, and flights resumed, with clashes continuing in multiple locations on the southern fringes of Tripoli.<ref name=IvesKirkpatrick/> On 8 April, the LGA said 19 of its soldiers died in recent days in the fighting in and around Tripoli, while a spokesman for the GNA's said that \"fighting in the south of the capital had killed at least 25 people, including fighters and civilians, and wounded 80.\"<ref name=\"reutersapril9look\"/>\n\nFrom the beginning of April 2019 to mid-May 2019, southern Tripoli's Yarmouk military camp/barracks had changed hands between the GNA and the LNA at least five times.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-libya-security-frontline-analysis/snatched-selfies-along-libyas-frontline-point-to-long-war-idUSKCN1SG0EN|title=Snatched selfies along Libya's frontline point to long war|agency=Reuters|author=Ulf Laessing|date=May 10, 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe LNA used [[BM-21 Grad]] [[Multiple rocket launcher|MRLs]] against GNA positions<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ansamed.info/ansamed/en/news/sections/generalnews/2019/04/08/haftar-launches-missiles-on-tripoli-us-withdraws_ea80eb6d-313d-4b42-b5de-2726c7cb48c1.html|title=Haftar launches missiles on Tripoli, US withdraws \u2013 General news|date=8 April 2019|website=ANSAMed|language=en|access-date=8 April 2019}}</ref> in retaliation for GNA airstrikes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/africa/un-backed-libya-govt-jets-strike-haftar-s-airbase/1444950|title=UN-backed Libya gov't jets strike Haftar's airbase|website=aa.com.tr|access-date=8 April 2019}}</ref> \n\nAccording to [[Media of Libya|Libya al-Ahrar TV]] as cited by ''[[The Libya Observer]]'', a team of French \"military experts\" arrived in [[Gharyan]] and created a \"control room to monitor the attack on Tripoli\".<ref name=\"LibObs_Frenchteam_Gharyan\">{{cite news|last1=Assad|first1=Abdulkader|title=UNSMIL says still working in Tripoli as France denies supporting Haftar's war |date=8 April 2019|publisher=[[The Libya Observer]]|url=https://www.libyaobserver.ly/news/unsmil-says-still-working-tripoli-france-denies-supporting-haftars-war|accessdate=9 April 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190412231328/https://www.libyaobserver.ly/news/unsmil-says-still-working-tripoli-france-denies-supporting-haftars-war|archivedate=12 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"LibObs_militaryteam_Gharyan\">{{cite web|title=French President telephones Sarraj after alleged link of his country in Tripoli war|publisher=[[The Libya Observer]]|date=9 April 2019|url=https://www.libyaobserver.ly/news/french-president-telephones-sarraj-after-alleged-link-his-country-tripoli-war|accessdate=9 April 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190409144720/https://www.libyaobserver.ly/news/french-president-telephones-sarraj-after-alleged-link-his-country-tripoli-war|archivedate=9 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n;10 April\nThe GNA reported bombing LNA targets within the LNA-held town of [[Gharyan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/Lyobserver/status/1115907987728752642|title=#Libya Air Force conducts airstrikes on military targets for eastern invaders of warlord Khalifa Haftar in the mountain city of Gharyan|last=Observer|first=The Libya|date=10 April 2019|website=@Lyobserver|language=en|access-date=10 April 2019}}</ref> The LNA announced that they have captured the 4th Brigade Headquarters in the town of Azizya after fierce fighting with the GNA.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/libyaalaan/status/1115927898223992833|title=#\u0644\u064a\u0628\u064a\u0627_\u0627\u0644\u0622\u0646{{!}} \u0627\u0644\u062c\u064a\u0634 \u0627\u0644\u0648\u0637\u0646\u064a \u064a\u0633\u064a\u0637\u0631 \u0639\u0644\u0649 \u0645\u0639\u0633\u0643\u0631 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0648\u0627\u0621 \u0627\u0644\u0631\u0627\u0628\u0639 \u0623\u0639\u0644\u0646\u062a \u0634\u0639\u0628\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0625\u0639\u0644\u0627\u0645 \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0631\u0628\u064a \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0627\u0628\u0639\u0629 \u0644\u0644\u0642\u064a\u0627\u062f\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0627\u0645\u0629 \u0644\u0644\u062c\u064a\u0634 \u0627\u0644\u0648\u0637\u0646\u064a\u060c \u0623\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0642\u0648\u0627\u062a \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u0644\u062d\u0629 \u0633\u064a\u0637\u0631\u062a \u0639\u0644\u0649 \u0645\u0639\u0633\u0643\u0631 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0648\u0627\u0621 \u0627\u0644\u0631\u0627\u0628\u0639 \u0628\u0645\u0646\u0637\u0642\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0632\u064a\u0632\u064a\u0629\u060c \u0628\u0639\u062f \u0645\u0639\u0627\u0631\u0643 \u0634\u0631\u0633\u0629 \u0648\u0627\u0634\u062a\u0628\u0627\u0643\u0627\u062a \u0639\u0646\u064a\u0641\u0629 \u062f\u0627\u0631\u062a \u0641\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0646\u0627\u0637\u0642 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u062d\u064a\u0637\u0629 \u0628\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0639\u0633\u0643\u0631.pic.twitter.com/zTgWTrE2Of|last=\u0627\u0644\u0622\u0646|first=\u0644\u064a\u0628\u064a\u0627|date=10 April 2019|website=@libyaalaan|language=ar|access-date=10 April 2019}}</ref> The [[Unhcr|UNHCR]] attempted to evacuate detained refugees from the Qasir bin Gashir detention center, after it became stuck in crossfire between the two sides.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/UNHCR_Arabic/status/1115902302949388290|title=\u0648\u0633\u0637 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0648\u0627\u062c\u0647\u0627\u062a \u0627\u0644\u062c\u0627\u0631\u064a\u0629 \u0641\u064a #\u0644\u064a\u0628\u064a\u0627\u060c \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0641\u0648\u0636\u064a\u0629 \u062a\u0646\u0642\u0644 \u0644\u0627\u062c\u0626\u064a\u0646 \u0645\u062d\u062a\u062c\u0632\u064a\u0646 \u0625\u0644\u0649 \u0645\u0646\u0627\u0637\u0642 \u0622\u0645\u0646\u0629.|last=\u0627\u0644\u0644\u0627\u062c\u0626\u064a\u0646|first=\u0645\u0641\u0648\u0636\u064a\u0629|date=10 April 2019|website=@UNHCR_Arabic|language=ar|access-date=10 April 2019}}</ref> Reports suggest most detainees were transferred to Sekah Road detention center, but around 120 people were left behind and were still in the Qasir bin Gashir detention center by the morning.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/amelgasir/status/1115933018332463104|title=Update on the Ain Zara detention center. The women were {{sic|transfered|nolink=y}} to Sekah Road detention center. Approx 120 migrants were left behind. They are still in the center, as seen in this photo, which is taken this morning. #Libya #Tripoli @ICRC_lby @UNHCRLibya @IntlCrimCourtpic.twitter.com/eQrlhBQ85O|last=El-Gasir|first=Ahmed|date=10 April 2019|website=@amelgasir|language=en|access-date=10 April 2019}}</ref> During the afternoon, the LNA air force conducted an airstrike against GNA targets near Tripoli airport.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/SkyNewsArabia_B/status/1115977526961221632|title=\u063a\u0627\u0631\u0629 \u062c\u0648\u064a\u0629 \u0644\u0644\u062c\u064a\u0634 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064a\u0628\u064a \u0639\u0644\u0649 \u062a\u062c\u0645\u0639 \u0644\u0644\u0645\u064a\u0644\u064a\u0634\u064a\u0627\u062a \u0628\u0645\u062d\u064a\u0637 \u0645\u0637\u0627\u0631 \u0637\u0631\u0627\u0628\u0644\u0633|last=\u0639\u0631\u0628\u064a\u0629-\u0627\u0644\u0622\u0646|first=\u0633\u0643\u0627\u064a \u0646\u064a\u0648\u0632|date=10 April 2019|website=@SkyNewsArabia_B|language=ar|access-date=10 April 2019}}</ref> By sunset, LNA spokesperson, Brig. Gen. Ahmed al-Mismari, stated that the LNA have secured al-Yarmouk camp and are advancing toward the Dabali military camp.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/SkyNewsArabia_B/status/1116035224339664897|title=\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u0645\u0627\u0631\u064a: \u0628\u0639\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0633\u064a\u0637\u0631\u0629 \u0639\u0644\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u064a\u0631\u0645\u0648\u0643 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0639\u0631\u0643\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0622\u0646 \u062a\u062f\u0648\u0631 \u062d\u0648\u0644 \u0645\u0639\u0633\u0643\u0631 \u0627\u0644\u062f\u0628\u0627\u0644\u064a|last=\u0639\u0631\u0628\u064a\u0629-\u0627\u0644\u0622\u0646|first=\u0633\u0643\u0627\u064a \u0646\u064a\u0648\u0632|date=10 April 2019|website=@SkyNewsArabia_B|language=ar|access-date=10 April 2019}}</ref> He also reported that the LNA have arrested pro-GNA \"african mercenaries\" at Tripoli Int'l Airport.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/AlainBRK/status/1116033392599097344|title=\u0639\u0627\u062c\u0644 {{!}} \u0627\u0644\u0645\u062a\u062d\u062f\u062b \u0628\u0627\u0633\u0645 \u0627\u0644\u062c\u064a\u0634 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064a\u0628\u064a: \u0645\u0637\u0627\u0631 #\u0637\u0631\u0627\u0628\u0644\u0633 \u0627\u0644\u062f\u0648\u0644\u064a \u062a\u062d\u062a \u0633\u064a\u0637\u0631\u062a\u0646\u0627 \u0648\u0642\u0628\u0636\u0646\u0627 \u0639\u0644\u0649 \u0645\u0631\u062a\u0632\u0642\u0629 \u0623\u0641\u0627\u0631\u0642\u0629. #\u0644\u064a\u0628\u064a\u0627|last=\u0639\u0627\u062c\u0644|first=\u0627\u0644\u0639\u064a\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062e\u0628\u0627\u0631\u064a\u0629-|date=10 April 2019|website=@AlainBRK|language=ar|access-date=10 April 2019}}</ref> Shortly thereafter, al-Mismari stated that the LNA have shot down a GNA [[Aero L-39 Albatros]] that attempted to relocate from [[Misrata]] to [[Tripoli]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/LibyasChannel/status/1116037375044530176|title=#\u0639\u0627\u062c\u0644 {{!}} \u0634\u0639\u0628\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0625\u0639\u0644\u0627\u0645 \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0631\u0628\u064a: \u0627\u0644\u0642\u0648\u0627\u062a \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u0644\u062d\u0629 \u062a\u0633\u0642\u0637 \u0637\u0627\u0626\u0631\u0629 \u062d\u0631\u0628\u064a\u0629 \u0627\u0646\u0637\u0644\u0642\u062a \u0645\u0646 \u0642\u0627\u0639\u062f\u0629 \u0645\u0635\u0631\u0627\u062a\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u062c\u0648\u064a\u0629 \u0628\u0627\u062a\u062c\u0627\u0647 \u0637\u0631\u0627\u0628\u0644\u0633 #\u0642\u0646\u0627\u0629_\u0644\u064a\u0628\u064a\u0627pic.twitter.com/QjT8BOOgRZ|last=\u0644\u064a\u0628\u064a\u0627|first=\u0642\u0646\u0627\u0629|date=10 April 2019|website=@LibyasChannel|language=ar|access-date=10 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/218Tv/status/1116041339089620995|title=#\u0639\u0627\u062c\u0644 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0648\u0627\u0621 #\u0623\u062d\u0645\u062f_\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u0645\u0627\u0631\u064a: \u0627\u0644\u0637\u0627\u0626\u0631\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u064a \u0623\u0633\u0642\u0637\u0646\u0627\u0647\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u064a\u0648\u0645 \u0646\u0648\u0639 L39 \u062e\u0631\u062c\u062a \u0645\u0646 \u0643\u0644\u064a\u0629 #\u0645\u0635\u0631\u0627\u062a\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u062c\u0648\u064a\u0629 #218TV|last=218TV|date=10 April 2019|website=@218Tv|language=ar|access-date=10 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n;11 April\nThe Chief of the GNA Tripoli Military Zone, Maj. Gen. Abdul-Basit Marwan, stated that the LNA were shelling GNA positions in southern Tripoli with [[BM-21 Grad]] [[Multiple rocket launcher|MRLs]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/Lyobserver/status/1116275327037210624|title=Chief of Tripoli Military Zone Major General Abdul-Basit Marwan says warlord Khalifa Haftar's armed groups are shelling southern #Tripoli areas with BM-21 Grad rockets in an attempt to drive #Libya Army forces backpic.twitter.com/YS1tCStxX7|last=Observer|first=The Libya|date=11 April 2019|website=@Lyobserver|language=en|access-date=11 April 2019}}</ref> The GNA claimed several airstrikes on LNA targets in Suq al-Khamis and Tarhuna city.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/Lyobserver/status/1116257802790547461|title=Breaking News: #Libya Air Force conducts airstrikes on targets for warlord Khalifa Haftar's armed groups in Souq Khamies town in south #Tripoli and in Tarhuna citypic.twitter.com/DyrZ30wZKe|last=Observer|first=The Libya|date=11 April 2019|website=@Lyobserver|language=en|access-date=11 April 2019}}</ref> The LNA retaliated by launching an airstrike on GNA targets in the contested Ayn Zara region.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/Lyobserver/status/1116288941391478787|title=Air force of eastern armed groups conducts an airstrike on Ein Zara region in southern #Tripoli in a bid to push #Libya Army forces backpic.twitter.com/bArS6ILZRo|last=Observer|first=The Libya|date=11 April 2019|website=@Lyobserver|language=en|access-date=11 April 2019}}</ref> A GNA spokesman reported that the GNA have recaptured Wadie Alrabie, Bridge 27, Bridge of Souq Al-Ahad and [[Tripoli International Airport]]. Brig. Gen. Al-Mismari, LNA spokesperson, reported that the \"things on the ground are in favour of the [Libyan National] [[Libyan National Army|army]],\" adding that they have seized 14 GNA armoured vehicles and tanks, positioning themselves a mere 2&nbsp;km from Tripoli's city centre after a GNA retreat. He stated that Tripoli Int'l Airport is \"still a fire zone,\" but did not comment on who controlled it at that time. He also promised to \"surprise everyone\" with a plan to seize all of [[Tripoli]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.middleeastmonitor.com/20190411-national-accord-government-regains-control-of-four-sites-in-tripoli-haftar-promises-surprise/|title=National Accord Government regains control of four sites in Tripoli; Haftar promises 'surprise'|date=11 April 2019|website=Middle East Monitor|language=en-GB|access-date=11 April 2019}}</ref> By nightfall, the GNA claimed that it negotiated the surrender of soldiers belonging to the LNA 8th brigade in Ayn Zara, after they were left without fuel or ammunition for more than a day.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/EanLibya/status/1116367480258211842|title=#\u0639\u0627\u062c\u0644 {{!}} \u0627\u0644\u0643\u062a\u064a\u0628\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u062b\u0627\u0645\u0646\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0627\u0628\u0639\u0629 \u0644\u0642\u0648\u0627\u062a \u062d\u0641\u062a\u0631 \u062a\u0633\u0644\u0645 \u0646\u0641\u0633\u0647\u0627 \u0628\u0639\u062a\u0627\u062f\u0647\u0627 \u0633\u0644\u0645\u064a\u064b\u0627 \u0644\u0642\u0648\u0627\u062a \u0627\u0644\u062c\u064a\u0634 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064a\u0628\u064a \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0627\u0628\u0639 \u0644\u0640\"\u062d\u0643\u0648\u0645\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0648\u0641\u0627\u0642\" \u0641\u064a \u0645\u062d\u0648\u0631 #\u0639\u064a\u0646_\u0632\u0627\u0631\u0629 \u2013 #\u0648\u0627\u062f\u064a_\u0627\u0644\u0631\u0628\u064a\u0639 \u0628\u0639\u062f \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0627\u0648\u0636 \u0625\u062b\u0631 \u0627\u0646\u0642\u0637\u0627\u0639 \u0627\u0644\u0625\u0645\u062f\u0627\u062f\u0627\u062a \u0648\u0627\u0644\u0648\u0642\u0648\u062f \u0639\u0646\u0647\u0627 \u0645\u0646\u0630 \u0627\u0644\u0623\u0645\u0633. #\u0639\u064a\u0646_\u0644\u064a\u0628\u064a\u0627pic.twitter.com/AnCHLOW4fK|last=\u0644\u064a\u0628\u064a\u0627|first=\u0639\u064a\u0646|date=11 April 2019|website=@EanLibya|language=ar|access-date=12 April 2019}}</ref> The LNA shelled the contested town of Al Swatani.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/libyaalahrartv/status/1116447209418104832|title=#\u0634\u0627\u0647\u062f {{!}} \u0642\u062a\u0644\u0649 \u0641\u064a \u0642\u0635\u0641 \u0644\u0642\u0648\u0627\u062a \u062d\u0641\u062a\u0631 \u0639\u0644\u0649 \u0645\u0646\u0627\u0632\u0644 \u0628\u0645\u0646\u0637\u0642\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0633\u0648\u0627\u0646\u064a #\u0627\u0644\u062d\u0631\u0628_\u0639\u0644\u0649_\u0637\u0631\u0627\u0628\u0644\u0633pic.twitter.com/4DyuD5WhTx|last=\u0627\u0644\u0623\u062d\u0631\u0627\u0631|first=Libya Alahrar TV-\u0642\u0646\u0627\u0629 \u0644\u064a\u0628\u064a\u0627|date=11 April 2019|website=@libyaalahrartv|language=ar|access-date=12 April 2019}}</ref> An LNA spokesman stated that the [[Libyan National Army]] has issued an arrest warrant for [[Fayez al-Sarraj]], head of the GNA.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/MaryFitzger/status/1116444433476661259|title=Spokesman for Haftar's LNA forces announces \"arrest warrant\" has been issued for head of UN-backed internationally recognized Government of National Accord (GNA) in Tripoli plus GNA-aligned military officers. Haftar's camp ups the ante...#Libya|last=Fitzgerald|first=Mary|date=11 April 2019|website=@MaryFitzger|language=en|access-date=12 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n;12 April\nThe LNA conducted an airstrike against the GNA in Abdel Samad Camp, south of [[Zuwarah]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/libyaalahrartv/status/1116625049501327361|title=#\u0639\u0627\u062c\u0644 {{!}} \u0637\u064a\u0631\u0627\u0646 #\u062d\u0641\u062a\u0631 \u064a\u0642\u0635\u0641 \u0645\u0639\u0633\u0643\u0631 \u0639\u0628\u062f\u0627\u0644\u0635\u0645\u062f \u062c\u0646\u0648\u0628 #\u0632\u0648\u0627\u0631\u0629 \u0648\u0625\u0635\u0627\u0628\u0629 \u0634\u062e\u0635 \u0628\u062c\u0631\u0648\u062d \u0637\u0641\u064a\u0641\u0629 #\u0627\u0644\u062d\u0631\u0628_\u0639\u0644\u0649_\u0637\u0631\u0627\u0628\u0644\u0633|last=\u0627\u0644\u0623\u062d\u0631\u0627\u0631|first=Libya Alahrar TV-\u0642\u0646\u0627\u0629 \u0644\u064a\u0628\u064a\u0627|date=12 April 2019|website=@libyaalahrartv|language=ar|access-date=12 April 2019}}</ref> Heavy gunfire and explosions were reported from downtown [[Tripoli]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/04/fighting-echoes-tripoli-thousands-continue-flee-190412101131619.html|title=Fighting echoes through Tripoli as thousands continue to flee|website=aljazeera.com|access-date=12 April 2019}}</ref> The LNA stated that they have received major military reinforcements, that they have killed dozens of GNA fighters in the previous day's offensive, and that the LNA 9th brigade is advancing in the Al-Khalla region. It also reported that several young GNA fighters defected to the LNA.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://aawsat.com/english/home/article/1675781/clashes-reach-tripoli-suburbs-islamists-rally-support|title=Clashes Reach Tripoli Suburbs as Islamists Rally for Support|website=Asharq AL-awsat|language=en|access-date=12 April 2019}}</ref> The LNA air force conducted air raids against GNA targets in Wadi Al Rabie, south of [[Tripoli]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/aawsat_News/status/1116683178025148416|title=\u0639\u0627\u062c\u0644 \u0645\u0646 #\u0644\u064a\u0628\u064a\u0627 {{!}} \u0637\u064a\u0631\u0627\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u062c\u064a\u0634 \u0627\u0644\u0648\u0637\u0646\u064a \u064a\u0646\u0641\u0630 \u063a\u0627\u0631\u0627\u062a \u062c\u0648\u064a\u0629 \u0641\u064a \u0645\u062d\u0648\u0631 \u0648\u0627\u062f\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0631\u0628\u064a\u0639 \u062c\u0646\u0648\u0628 #\u0637\u0631\u0627\u0628\u0644\u0633|last=\u0627\u0644\u0623\u0648\u0633\u0637|first=\u0635\u062d\u064a\u0641\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0634\u0631\u0642|date=12 April 2019|website=@aawsat_News|language=ar|access-date=12 April 2019}}</ref> In the late afternoon, the LNA conducted airstrikes against a GNA military camp,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/SkyNewsArabia_B/status/1116702748215513088|title=\u0645\u0635\u0627\u062f\u0631\u0646\u0627: \u0633\u0644\u0627\u062d \u0627\u0644\u062c\u0648 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0627\u0628\u0639 \u0644\u0644\u062c\u064a\u0634 \u0627\u0644\u0648\u0637\u0646\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064a\u0628\u064a \u064a\u0642\u0635\u0641 \u0645\u0639\u0633\u0643\u0631\u0627 \u062a\u0627\u0628\u0639\u0627 \u0644\u0644\u0645\u064a\u0644\u064a\u0634\u064a\u0627\u062a \u0641\u064a \u0645\u0646\u0637\u0642\u0629 \u062a\u0627\u062c\u0648\u0631\u0627\u0621 \u0634\u0645\u0627\u0644 \u0634\u0631\u0642\u064a \u0637\u0631\u0627\u0628\u0644\u0633|last=\u0639\u0631\u0628\u064a\u0629-\u0627\u0644\u0622\u0646|first=\u0633\u0643\u0627\u064a \u0646\u064a\u0648\u0632|date=12 April 2019|website=@SkyNewsArabia_B|language=ar|access-date=12 April 2019}}</ref> as well as an arms cache in the North-East Tripoli neighbourhood of Tajura.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/AlainBRK/status/1116704253282799616|title=\u0639\u0627\u062c\u0644 {{!}} \u0637\u064a\u0631\u0627\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u062c\u064a\u0634 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064a\u0628\u064a \u064a\u062f\u0645\u0631 \u0645\u062e\u0632\u0646 \u0644\u0623\u0633\u0644\u062d\u0629 \u0645\u064a\u0644\u064a\u0634\u064a\u0627\u062a #\u0637\u0631\u0627\u0628\u0644\u0633 \u0641\u064a \u062a\u0627\u062c\u0648\u0631\u0627\u0621 \u0634\u0645\u0627\u0644 \u0634\u0631\u0642\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0627\u0635\u0645\u0629. #\u0644\u064a\u0628\u064a\u0627|last=\u0639\u0627\u062c\u0644|first=\u0627\u0644\u0639\u064a\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062e\u0628\u0627\u0631\u064a\u0629-|date=12 April 2019|website=@AlainBRK|language=ar|access-date=12 April 2019}}</ref> Explosions were reported at GNA-held [[Mitiga International Airport]]. Conflicting reports emerged as to whether they were from an LNA airstrike<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/AlkhaleejOnline/status/1116702765496061952|title=\u0648\u