overnment\n! rowspan=\"2\" width=\"40px\"| Size\n|-\n! width=\"85px\"| Votes\n! width=\"50px\"| %\n! width=\"40px\"| \u00b1[[Percentage point|pp]]\n! width=\"100px\"| Seats won\n! width=\"40px\"| +/\u2212\n|-\n! [[Azores]]\n! [[2016 Azorean regional election|2016]]\n| 28,793\n| 30.9% \n| {{decrease}}2.1\n| {{composition bar|19|57|hex={{Social Democratic Party (Portugal)/meta/color}}}}\n| {{Decrease}}1\n| style=\"background-color:#FFCCCC\"| Opposition\n| {{Steady}} 2nd\n|-\n! [[Madeira]]\n! [[2019 Madeiran regional election|2019]]\n| 56,448\n| 39.4%\n| {{decrease}}4.9\n| {{composition bar|21|47|hex={{Social Democratic Party (Portugal)/meta/color}}}}\n| {{Decrease}}3\n| style=\"background-color:#CCFFCC\"| Coalition gov't<br><small>PSD-[[Democratic and Social Centre \u2013 People's Party|CDS\u2013PP]]</small>\n| {{Steady}} '''1st'''\n|}\n\n==List of leaders==\n{{Col-begin|width=100%}}\n{{Col-break}}\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!\n! Leader{{ref label|Leaders|A|A}}\n! From\n! To\n|-\n| 1st\n| [[Francisco S\u00e1 Carneiro]] <small>(1st time)</small>\n| 6 May 1974\n| 29 January 1978{{ref label|Leaders|B|B}}\n|-\n| 2nd\n| [[Ant\u00f3nio de Sousa Franco]]\n| 29 January 1978\n| 2 July 1978\n|-\n| 3rd\n| [[:pt:Jos\u00e9 Men\u00e9res Pimentel|Jos\u00e9 Men\u00e9res Pimentel]]\n| 2 July 1978\n| 29 April 1979\n|-\n| 4th\n| {{nowrap|[[Francisco S\u00e1 Carneiro]] <small>(2nd time)</small>}}\n| 29 April 1979\n| 4 December 1980\n|-\n| 5th\n| [[Francisco Pinto Balsem\u00e3o]]\n| 9 January 1981\n| 27 February 1983\n|-\n| 6th\n| [[:pt:Nuno Rodrigues dos Santos|Nuno Rodrigues dos Santos]]\n| 27 February 1983\n| 4 April 1984\n|-\n| 7th\n| [[Carlos Mota Pinto]]\n| 4 April 1984\n| 7 May 1985\n|-\n| 8th\n| [[An\u00edbal Cavaco Silva]]\n| 2 June 1985\n| 19 February 1995\n|-\n| 9th\n| [[Fernando Nogueira]]\n| 19 February 1995\n| 29 March 1996\n|-\n| 10th\n| [[Marcelo Rebelo de Sousa]]\n| 31 March 1996\n| 27 May 1999\n|-\n| 11th\n| [[Jos\u00e9 Manuel Dur\u00e3o Barroso]]\n| 27 May 1999\n| 15 July 2004\n|-\n| 12th\n| [[Pedro Santana Lopes]]\n| 15 July 2004\n| 22 February 2005\n|-\n| 13th\n| [[Lu\u00eds Marques Mendes]]\n| 24 February 2005\n| {{nowrap|28 September 2007}}\n|-\n| 14th\n| [[Lu\u00eds Filipe Menezes]]\n| {{nowrap|28 September 2007}}\n| 31 May 2008\n|-\n| 15th\n| [[Manuela Ferreira Leite]]\n| 31 May 2008\n| 26 March 2010\n|-\n| 16th\n| [[Pedro Passos Coelho]]\n| 26 March 2010\n| 18 February 2018\n|-\n| 17th\n| [[Rui Rio]]\n| 18 February 2018\n| ''Incumbent''\n|-\n| colspan=4| <small>{{note|Leaders|A}} Leaders until Pinto Balsem\u00e3o had the title of General-Secretary, which from then on<br> became the title of the second-in-command, with the leader's title being the one of President.<br>{{note|Leaders|B}} [[:pt:Em\u00eddio Guerreiro|Em\u00eddio Guerreiro]] temporarily replaced S\u00e1 Carneiro in 1975 due to health reasons.</small>\n|}\n{{Col-break}}\n\n<timeline>\nImageSize  = width:400 height:500\nPlotArea   = width:350  height:450 left:50 bottom:50\nLegend    = columns:3 left:50 top:25 columnwidth:50\n\nDateFormat = yyyy\nPeriod     = from:1975 till:2020\nTimeAxis   = orientation:vertical\nScaleMajor = unit:year increment:5 start:1975\n\n# there is no automatic collision detection,\n# so shift texts up or down manually to avoid overlap\n\nColors=\n  id:PS  value:pink    legend:PS\n  id:PSD  value:orange legend:PSD\n\nDefine $dx = 25 # shift text to right side of bar\nDefine $dy = -5 # adjust height\n\nPlotData=\n\n  bar:Leader color:red width:30 mark:(line,white) align:left fontsize:7\n\n  from:1975  till:1978 shift:($dx,$dy)    color:PSD    text:[[Francisco S\u00e1 Carneiro]]\n  from:1978  till:1978 shift:($dx,$dy)    color:PSD    text:[[Ant\u00f3nio de Sousa Franco]]\n  from:1978  till:1980 shift:($dx,$dy)    color:PSD    text:[[Francisco S\u00e1 Carneiro]]\n  from:1980  till:1983 shift:($dx,$dy)    color:PSD    text:[[Francisco Pinto Balsem\u00e3o]]\n  from:1983  till:1984 shift:($dx,$dy)    color:PSD    text:[[Nuno Rodrigues dos Santos