]]\n  from:2004  till:2005 shift:($dx,$dy)    color:PSD    text:[[Pedro Santana Lopes|Santana Lopes]]\n  from:2005  till:2009 shift:($dx,$dy)    color:PS     text:[[Jos\u00e9 S\u00f3crates|S\u00f3crates]] I\n  from:2009  till:2011 shift:($dx,$dy)    color:PS     text:S\u00f3crates II\n  from:2011  till:2015 shift:($dx,$dy)    color:PSD    text:[[Pedro Passos Coelho|Passos Coelho]] \n  from:2015  till:2019 shift:($dx,$dy)     color:PS     text:[[Ant\u00f3nio Costa|Costa]] I\n  from:2019  till:end shift:($dx,$dy)     color:PS     text:[[Ant\u00f3nio Costa|Costa]] II\n\n</timeline>\n{{col-end}}\n\n==List of Secretaries-General (second-in-command)==\n*[[Joaquim Magalh\u00e3es Mota]] (1976\u20131978; as President)\n*[[S\u00e9rvulo Correia]] (1978; as President)\n*[[Am\u00e2ndio de Azevedo]] (1978\u20131979; as President)\n*[[Ant\u00f3nio Capucho]] (1979\u20131984; as President until 1983)\n*[[Antunes da Silva]] (1984\u20131985)\n*[[Dias Loureiro]] (1985\u20131990)\n*[[Falc\u00e3o e Cunha]] (1990\u20131992)\n*[[Nunes Liberato]] (1992\u20131995)\n*[[Azevedo Soares]] (1995\u20131996)\n*[[Rui Rio]] (1996\u20131997)\n*[[Horta e Costa]] (1997\u20131998)\n*Ant\u00f3nio Capucho (1998)\n*[[Torres Pereira]] (1998\u20131999)\n*[[Jos\u00e9 Lu\u00eds Arnaut]] (1999\u20132004)\n*[[Miguel Relvas]] (2004\u20132005)\n*[[Miguel Macedo]] (2005\u20132007)\n*[[Ribau Esteves]] (2007\u20132008)\n*[[Lu\u00eds Marques Guedes]] (2008\u20132010)\n*Miguel Relvas (2010\u20132011)\n*[[Jos\u00e9 Matos Rosa]] (2011\u20132018)\n*[[Feliciano Barreiras Duarte]] (2018)\n*[[Jos\u00e9 Silvano]] (2018\u2013present)\nSource:<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oRpZr4nE_go Filme Secret\u00e1rios Gerais PSD 1975 2012], Youtube.com</ref>\n\n==Prime Ministers==\n*[[Francisco S\u00e1 Carneiro]]: 1979\u20131980\n*[[Francisco Pinto Balsem\u00e3o]]: 1981\u20131983\n*[[An\u00edbal Cavaco Silva]]: 1985\u20131995\n*[[Jos\u00e9 Manuel Dur\u00e3o Barroso]]: 2002\u20132004\n*[[Pedro Santana Lopes]]: 2004\u20132005\n*[[Pedro Passos Coelho]]: 2011\u20132015\n\n==Presidents of the Republic==\n*[[An\u00edbal Cavaco Silva]]: 2006\u20132016\n*[[Marcelo Rebelo de Sousa]]: 2016\u2013present\n\n==See also==\n*[[Politics of Portugal]]\n*[[List of political parties in Portugal]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Partido Popular Democr\u00e1tico \u2013 Partido Social Democrata}}\n*[http://www.psd.pt Social Democratic Party] \u2013 official website {{in lang|pt}}\n*[http://jsd.pt/ Social Democratic Youth] \u2013 official website {{in lang|pt}}\n*[http://www.tsd.pt/ Social Democratic Workers] \u2013 official website {{in lang|pt}}\n\n{{Portuguese parties}}\n{{European People's Party}}\n\n[[Category:1974 establishments in Portugal]]\n[[Category:Conservative parties in Portugal]]\n[[Category:Liberal conservative parties]]\n[[Category:Liberal parties in Portugal]]\n[[Category:Member parties of the European People's Party]]\n[[Category:Organisations based in Lisbon]]\n[[Category:Political parties established in 1974]]\n[[Category:Political parties in Portugal]]\n", "text_old": "{{use dmy dates|date=January 2013}}\n{{Infobox political party\n| name = Social Democratic Party\n| native_name = Partido Social Democrata\n| colorcode = {{Social Democratic Party (Portugal)/meta/color}}\n| logo = [[File:Partido Social Democrata Logo.svg|260px]]\n| abbreviation = '''PPD/PSD'''<ref name=\"TC\">[http://www.tribunalconstitucional.pt/tc/partidos.html \"Partidos registados e suas denomina\u00e7\u00f5es, siglas e s\u00edmbolos\"] [[Constitutional Court of Portugal|Tribunal Constitucional]] {{in lang|pt}}.</ref>\n| president = [[Rui Rio]]\n| secretary_general = Jos\u00e9 Silvano\n| founder = [[Francisco S\u00e1 Carneiro]]\n| foundation = {{start date and age|1974|5|6|df=yes}}\n| legalized = {{start date and age|1975|1|17|df=yes}}<ref name=\"TC\"/>\n| headquarters = Rua de S. Caetano \u00e0 Lapa, 9,<br> 1249-087 [[Lisbon|Lisboa]]\n| newspaper = ''[[Povo Livre]]''\n| youth_wing = [