\"|{{decrease}}19\n| style=\"background-color:#CCFFCC\"| Minority gov't {{small|(2015)}}\n| rowspan=\"2\"|'''1st'''\n|-\n| style=\"background-color:#FFCCCC\"| Opposition {{small|(2015-19)}}\n|-\n! [[2019 Portuguese legislative election|2019]]\n| 1,454,283 \n| 27.8%\n| \n| {{Composition bar|79|230|hex={{Social Democratic Party (Portugal)/meta/color}}}}\n| {{decrease}}10\n| style=\"background-color:#FFCCCC\"| Opposition \n| 2nd\n| [[Rui Rio]]\n|-\n|}\n\n===European Parliament===\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:100%; line-height:16px;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" width=\"50px\"| Election\n! colspan=\"5\"| [[European Parliament]]\n! rowspan=\"2\" width=\"40px\"| Size\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Candidate\n|-\n! width=\"85px\"| Votes\n! width=\"50px\"| %\n! width=\"40px\"| \u00b1[[Percentage point|pp]]\n! width=\"100px\"| Seats won\n! width=\"40px\"| +/\n|-\n! [[1987 European Parliament election in Portugal|1987]]\n| 2,111,828 \t\n| 37.5%\n| \n| {{Composition bar|10|24|hex={{Social Democratic Party (Portugal)/meta/color}}}}\n| \n| '''1st'''\n| [[Pedro Santana Lopes]]\n|-\n! [[1989 European Parliament election in Portugal|1989]]\n| 1,358,958\t\n| 32.8%\n| {{decrease}}4.7\n| {{Composition bar|9|24|hex={{Social Democratic Party (Portugal)/meta/color}}}}\n| {{decrease}}1\n| '''1st'''\n| [[Ant\u00f3nio Capucho]]\n|-\n! [[1994 European Parliament election in Portugal|1994]]\n| 1,046,918\t\n| 34.4%\n| {{increase}}1.6\n| {{Composition bar|9|25|hex={{Social Democratic Party (Portugal)/meta/color}}}}\n| {{steady}}0\n| 2nd\n| [[Eurico de Melo]]\n|-\n! [[1999 European Parliament election in Portugal|1999]]\n| 1,078,528 \n| 31.1%\n| {{decrease}}3.3\n| {{Composition bar|9|25|hex={{Social Democratic Party (Portugal)/meta/color}}}}\n| {{steady}}0\n| 2nd\n| [[Jos\u00e9 Pacheco Pereira]]\n|-\n! [[2004 European Parliament election in Portugal|2004]]\n| colspan=\"3\"| ''w. [[For\u00e7a Portugal]]''\n| {{Composition bar|7|24|hex={{Social Democratic Party (Portugal)/meta/color}}}}\n| {{decrease}}2\n| 2nd\n| [[Jo\u00e3o de Deus Pinheiro]]\n|-\n! [[2009 European Parliament election in Portugal|2009]]\n| 1,131,744\n| 31.7%\n| \n| {{Composition bar|8|22|hex={{Social Democratic Party (Portugal)/meta/color}}}}\n| {{increase}}1\n| '''1st'''\n|  rowspan=\"3\"|[[Paulo Rangel]]\n|-\n! [[2014 European Parliament election in Portugal|2014]]\n| colspan=\"3\"| ''w. [[Portugal Alliance|Alian\u00e7a Portugal]]''\n| {{Composition bar|6|21|hex={{Social Democratic Party (Portugal)/meta/color}}}}\n| {{decrease}}2\n| 2nd\n|-\n! [[2019 European Parliament election in Portugal|2019]]\n| 727,224 \n| 21.9%\n| \n| {{Composition bar|6|21|hex={{Social Democratic Party (Portugal)/meta/color}}}}\n| {{steady}}0\n| 2nd\n|}\n\n===Regional Assemblies===\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:100%; line-height:16px;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" width=\"50px\"| Region\n! rowspan=\"2\" width=\"50px\"| Election\n! colspan=\"5\"| [[Autonomous Regions of Portugal|Regional Assemblies]]\n! rowspan=\"2\" width=\"170px\"| Government\n! rowspan=\"2\" width=\"40px\"| Size\n|-\n! width=\"85px\"| Votes\n! width=\"50px\"| %\n! width=\"40px\"| \u00b1[[Percentage point|pp]]\n! width=\"100px\"| Seats won\n! width=\"40px\"| +/\u2212\n|-\n! [[Azores]]\n! [[2016 Azorean regional election|2016]]\n| 28,793\n| 30.9% \n| {{decrease}}2.1\n| {{composition bar|19|57|hex={{Social Democratic Party (Portugal)/meta/color}}}}\n| {{Decrease}}1\n| style=\"background-color:#FFCCCC\"| Opposition\n| {{Steady}} 2nd\n|-\n! [[Madeira]]\n! [[2019 Madeiran regional election|2019]]\n| 56,448\n| 39.4%\n| {{decrease}}4.9\n| {{composition bar|21|47|hex={{Social Democratic Party (Portugal)/meta/color}}}}\n| {{Decrease}}3\n| style=\"background-color:#CCFFCC\"| Coalition gov't<br><small>PSD-[[Democratic and Social Centre \u2013 People's Party|CDS\u2013PP]]</small>\n| {{Steady}} '''1st'''\n|}\n\n==List of leaders==\n{{Col-begin|width=100%}}\n{{Col-break}}\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!\n! Leader{{ref label|Leaders|A|A}}\n! From\n! To\n|-\n| 1st\n| [[Francisco S\u00e1 Carneiro]] <small>(1st time)</small>\n| 6 May 1974\n| 29 January 1978{{ref label|Leaders|B|B}}\n|-\n| 2nd\n| [[Ant\u00f3nio de Sousa Franco]]\n| 29 January 1978\n| 2 July 1978\n|-\n| 3rd\n| [[:pt:Jos\u00e9 Men\u00e9res Pimentel|Jos\u00e9 Men\u00e9res Pimentel]]\n| 2 July 1978\n| 29 April 1979\n|-\n| 4th\n| {{nowrap|[[Francisco S\u00e1 Carneiro]] <small>(2nd time)</small>}}\n| 29 April 1979\n| 4 December 1980\n|-\n| 5th\n| [[Francisco Pinto Balsem\u00e3o]]\n| 9 January 1981\n| 27 February 1983\n|-\n| 6th\n| [[:pt:Nuno Rodrigues dos Santos|Nuno Rodrigues dos Santos]]\n| 27 February 1983\n| 4 April 1984\n|-\n| 7th\n| [[Carlos Mota Pinto]]\n| 4 April 1984\n| 7 May 1985\n|-\n| 8th\n| [[An\u00edbal Cavaco Silva]]\n| 2 June 1985\n| 19 February 1995\n|-\n| 9th\n| [[Fernando Nogueira]]\n| 19 February 1995\n| 29 March 1996\n|-\n| 10th\n| [[Marcelo Rebelo de Sousa]]\n| 31 March 1996\n| 27 May 1999\n|-\n| 11th\n| [[Jos\u00e9 Manuel Dur\u00e3o Barroso]]\n| 27 May 1999\n| 15 July 2004\n|-\n| 12th\n| [[Pedro Santana Lopes]]\n| 15 July 2004\n| 22 February 2005\n|-\n| 13th\n| [[Lu\u00eds Marques Mendes]]\n| 24 February 2005\n| {{nowrap|28 September 2007}}\n|-\n| 14th\n| [[Lu\u00eds Filipe Menezes]]\n| {{nowrap|28 September 2007}}\n| 31 May 2008\n|-\n| 15th\n| [[Manuela Ferreira Leite]]\n| 31 May 2008\n| 26 March 2010\n|-\n| 16th\n| [[Pedro Passos Coelho]]\n| 26 March 2010\n| 18 February 2018\n|-\n| 17th\n| [[Rui Rio]]\n| 18 February 2018\n| ''Incumbent''\n|-\n| colspan=4| <small>{{note|Leaders|A}} Leaders until Pinto Balsem\u00e3o had the title of General-Secretary, which from then on<br> became the title of the second-in-command, with the leader's title being the one of President.<br>{{note|Leaders|B}} [[:pt:Em\u00eddio Guerreiro|Em\u00eddio Guerreiro]] temporarily replaced S\u00e1 Carneiro in 1975 due to health reasons.</small>\n|}\n{{Col-break}}\n\n<timeline>\nImageSize  = width:400 height:500\nPlotArea   = width:350  heig